SIMPLE: spotless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spotless
<hw>Spot"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Without a spot; especially, free
from reproach or impurity; pure; untainted; innocent; <as>as, a
<ex>spotless</ex> mind; <ex>spotless</ex> behavior</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>spotless</qex> virgin, and a faultless wife.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Blameless; unspotted; unblemished; pure;
immaculate; irreproachable. See <er>Blameless</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Spot"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Spot"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spotlight</ent>⟦br⟧
